<div class="wp-block-columns"><!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"level":5,"UAGDay":[]} -->
<h5 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>UPDATED: Conference Request &amp; Reporting Form</strong></h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Please note there is an updated conference request and reporting form on OVW's website should you be preparing and planning to host in-person events. Also available on the website are conference cost guidelines, form instructions, and frequently asked questions. If you have questions or need help, please email Neelam J. Patel, OVW, at&nbsp;<a rel="noreferrer noopener" href="mailto:ovw.techassistance@usdoj.gov?subject=TA2TA%20Newsletter%3A%20CRF%20Help" target="_blank"></a><a href="mailto:ovw.techassistance@usdoj.gov">ovw.techassistance@usdoj.gov</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:column -->

<!-- wp:column -->
<div class="wp-block-column"><!-- wp:heading {"level":5,"UAGDay":[]} -->
<h5 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>FY 2022 Training and TA Initiative Orientation</strong></h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The U.S. Department of Justice Office on Violence Against Women will be hosting the FY 2022 Training and Technical Assistance Initiative (TA Initiative) orientation as a series of webinars. Per the special conditions, the orientation is required for new TA provider organizations (key project staff and staff responsible for the management of the award) as well as any new staff of current TA projects.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>There are two registration links: 1) Webinars specific for the TA Initiative and 2) OVW&nbsp;office-wide webinars.<br><strong>November 10, 2022: Training and TA Initiative Overview and TA2TA</strong><br>10:00am PT | 11:00am MT | 12:00pm CT | 1:00pm ET (1.5 hours)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>November 14, 2022: Grants Financial Management Division</strong><br>10:00am PT | 11:00am MT | 12:00pm CT | 1:00pm ET (2 hours)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>November 16, 2022: Virtual Training and Technical Assistance</strong><br>10:00am PT | 11:00am MT | 12:00pm CT | 1:00pm ET (1.5 hours)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>November 30, 2022: Accessibility and Language Access for TA Providers</strong><br>10:00am PT | 11:00am MT | 12:00pm CT | 1:00pm ET (1.5 hours)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>For the OVW office-wide webinars, TA providers are required to attend the Civil Rights Obligations, the Overview of Grant Fraud Audits, and the Overview of Grant&nbsp;Fraud Investigations webinars. The other office-wide webinars are optional for TA providers as they are tailored specifically for grantees.<br><strong>December 13, 2022: Overview of Grant Fraud Investigations</strong><br>10:00am PT | 11:00am MT | 12:00pm CT | 1:00pm ET (1 hour)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>December 14, 2022: Overview of Grant Award Audits</strong><br>10:00am PT | 11:00am MT | 12:00pm CT | 1:00pm ET (1.5 hours)</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>December 15, 2022: Civil Rights Obligations of Federal Recipients&nbsp;<br>of Financial Assistance</strong><br>10:00am PT | 11:00am MT | 12:00pm CT | 1:00pm ET (1.5 hour)<br><strong><em>Please note that new TA provider organizations will receive a separate invitation from OVW.</em></strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>
<!-- /wp:column --></div>
